{"fingerprint": "6045096a6e626c61a4988d0fa8660d5fa1a925c9", "package": "jac-scale", "file": "jac/jaclang/scale/config/plugin_config.jac", "rule": "dead-code", "summary": "This ~492-line file defines JacScalePluginConfig, a static schema/metadata-description class (get_plugin_metadata, get_config_schema) that re-describes every default already declared in config/impl/config_loader.impl.jac's get_default_config(), as a verbose nested dict. Grepped the whole repo for JacScalePluginConfig and found only its own declaration line \u2014 nothing imports, instantiates, or calls its static methods, including its own test suite. Sibling plugin-config classes elsewhere in the monorepo (JacMcpPluginConfig, byllm's) are exercised by jac/tests/cli/test_mcp.jac; this one has zero references anywhere. Entire file can be deleted.", "score": 1230.0, "est_loc_saved": 492, "confidence": 5, "risk": 2, "branch": "nightshift/2026-07-14/dead-plugin-config", "status": "new", "attempts": 0, "first_seen": "2026-07-14", "last_seen": "2026-07-14"}
{"fingerprint": "6045096a6e626c61a4988d0fa8660d5fa1a925c9", "package": "jac-scale", "file": "jac/jaclang/scale/config/plugin_config.jac", "rule": "dead-code", "summary": "This ~492-line file defines JacScalePluginConfig, a static schema/metadata-description class (get_plugin_metadata, get_config_schema) that re-describes every default already declared in config/impl/config_loader.impl.jac's get_default_config(), as a verbose nested dict. Grepped the whole repo for JacScalePluginConfig and found only its own declaration line \u2014 nothing imports, instantiates, or calls its static methods, including its own test suite. Sibling plugin-config classes elsewhere in the monorepo (JacMcpPluginConfig, byllm's) are exercised by jac/tests/cli/test_mcp.jac; this one has zero references anywhere. Entire file can be deleted.", "score": 1230.0, "est_loc_saved": 492, "confidence": 5, "risk": 2, "branch": "nightshift/2026-07-14/dead-plugin-config", "status": "drafted", "attempts": 0, "first_seen": "2026-07-14", "last_seen": "2026-07-14"}
{"fingerprint": "b694663c06a6e6e6070533fd18f4de958d64ef9b", "package": "jac-byllm", "file": "jac/jaclang/byllm/plugin_config.jac", "rule": "dead-code", "summary": "The entire 169-line file defines `JacByllmPluginConfig` with `get_plugin_metadata()`/`get_config_schema()` static methods, but nothing in the repo calls either method on this class. Grepped the whole repo for `JacByllmPluginConfig` (case-sensitive) and the only hit is the definition itself; grepped for `.get_config_schema(` and `.get_plugin_metadata(` repo-wide and every call site targets a different module's sibling class (`JacMcpPluginConfig` in `jac/tests/cli/test_mcp.jac`) \u2014 byllm's own class has zero callers, including in its own tests. Actual byllm config plumbing goes through the entirely separate `JacByllmConfig`/`get_byllm_config()` in `config_loader.jac` + `impl/config_loader.impl.jac`, which is what every runtime call site (`llm.jac`, `basellm.impl.jac`, `mtir.impl.jac`, `cli/impl/ai_agent.impl.jac`, etc.) actually imports and uses. Confirming this is stale, not just unwired: the hand-written schema in this dead file omits several sections that exist in the real, live `get_default_config()` (`parallel`, `streaming`, `fallback`, and most of `compaction`/`local`), proving nobody has kept it in sync because nothing reads it. It is nonetheless actively harmful: `jac/jaclang/publish/runtime_vendor.jac` lists `\"jaclang.byllm.plugin_config\"` in `_BYLLM_SEEDS`, so this dead module and its stale schema dict get vendored into every published/ejected byllm app for no functional benefit.", "score": 845.0, "est_loc_saved": 169, "confidence": 5, "risk": 1, "branch": "nightshift/2026-07-19/dead-plugin-config", "status": "new", "attempts": 0, "first_seen": "2026-07-19", "last_seen": "2026-07-19"}
